    <item>
      <title>Word Lens: Translation using Augmented Reality</title>
      <link>http://konigi.com/blog/word-lens-translation-using-augmented-reality/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Dec 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://konigi.com/blog/word-lens-translation-using-augmented-reality/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;video&#34;&gt;
&lt;object width=&#34;610&#34; height=&#34;367&#34;&gt;&lt;param name=&#34;movie&#34; value=&#34;http://www.youtube.com/v/h2OfQdYrHRs?fs=1&amp;amp;hl=en_US&#34;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name=&#34;allowFullScreen&#34; value=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name=&#34;allowscriptaccess&#34; value=&#34;always&#34;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;embed src=&#34;http://www.youtube.com/v/h2OfQdYrHRs?fs=1&amp;amp;hl=en_US&#34; type=&#34;application/x-shockwave-flash&#34; allowscriptaccess=&#34;always&#34; allowfullscreen=&#34;true&#34; width=&#34;610&#34; height=&#34;367&#34;&gt;&lt;/embed&gt;&lt;/object&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is one of the most practical uses of augmented reality I&amp;rsquo;ve seen. &lt;a href=&#34;http://questvisual.com/&#34;&gt;Word Lens&lt;/a&gt; translates text you capture from an iPhone&amp;rsquo;s camera to another language. I think it&amp;rsquo;s only Spanish-English/English-Spanish at the moment, and $4.99 per language. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re skeptical, as some YouTubers seem to be in the comments, you can &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.flickr.com/photos/jibbajabba/tags/wordlens/&#34;&gt;see an example&lt;/a&gt; of the translation I did on my phone of an English magazine page to Spanish. Works best on big text, and probably most practical for signage. I need this for trips to Italy (my Italian is rough), so hopefully Italian will be available in the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://questvisual.com/&#34;&gt;http://questvisual.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
