&lt;p&gt;Microsoft has been doing some interesting work with Bing Maps. The augmented reality demos at the TED conference this week generated some buzz. The photo and video overlays were cool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We see this space, three-dimensional environment as being a canvas on which all sorts of applications can play out,&amp;rdquo; says Bing Maps&amp;rsquo; Blaise Aguera y Arcas. &amp;ldquo;Maps, directions are really just one of them.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

